78 degrees and humid. Large cumuli with hazy sun. Some yellow bloom in water.
80 degrees- some clouds. Saw a loon and heron while enroute. Beaver or muskrat mound in narrows.

column1: Loon surfaced near the boat on the return to dock.(Very large male)

column2: Hazy sun. Saw a family of 4 loons south of the narrows. There were 2 adults and 2 babies.
68 degrees- sunny- light northwest winds. Saw no wildlife. Some bloom on water near shore. Lake is about 3 inches low. Very quiet!
Temperature 42 degrees- bright sun- moderate north wind. Last test for 2007.

column1: Firsts: Robin 4/5- Juncos 4/7- Geese 4/7- Peeper frogs 4/21- Bear 4/27- Loon 5/4-
Wren 5/10- Hummingbirds and Orioles 5/12  53 degrees- clear w/some wind- marker dates: ice out 4/28

column2: 67 degrees- Light winds and scattered clouds. First bullfrogs 6/14
Mostly sunny- 72 degrees. Saw an adult loon and two chicks.
Hazy sun: saw one loon and one gull:nosurface weeds at cebter of lake as in past years. Hazy sun: saw one loon and one gull:nosurface weeds at cebter of lake as in past years.
Warm 72 degrees: Saw one Loon: Tree colors about 40 %: Never got to 90 degrees all summer.

Temp 70 degrees- sunny with large cumulus clouds. Ice out 4/20- first observations: chipmunk-3/16- black birds-3-23- robin-3/30- geese-4/4- wren-4-17- mosquitos-4-18- osprey-4/18- peeper frogs-4/23- loon-4/24- oriole-5/8- humming birds-5/19- dragonflies-5/28- bullfrogs-6/11.
Sunny and 75 degrees.Large patches of weeds on surface where there are usually bullrushes. Probably northern millfoil.
Saw 2 loons with 2 babies. Sunny and 82 degrees. Light wind.
Sunny- 76 degrees- very heavy algae bloom along shore at north end - extend out 40 to 50 feet from shore.
Partly cloudy-48 degrees-some wind. Saw 3 loons. Had 1.5" allday rain yesterday.
Sunny-42 degrees-some wind. Saw 1 loon. It tried to fly but couldn't get aloft.
Partly cloudy 50 degrees- Ice out:Apr 2- First sightings: Racoon Feb. 27- Blackbirds Mar. 19- Geese Mar. 25- Ducks Mar. 25- Robins Mar. 30- Peeper frogs Apr. 4- Loons Apr. 23
Hazy sun - 62 degrees - light wind - Observed 2 sets of adult Loon pairs.
Puffy clouds - 77 degrees - light wind - Saw 1 blue heron- but no loons seen this time.
Sunny -some wind - 75 degrees. Had 1/4 inche rain the previous day. No wildlife seen.

Sunny-moderate wind-58 degrees. Notable dates: Nov. 27- 2010-Lake frozen. Mar. 18th- 2011-Redwing Blackbirds back. Apr. 9th-Seagulls- Canada Geese and robins. Apr. 18th-Mallard Ducks. Apr. 25th-Loon and Spring Peeper Frogs. April 26th-Ice out! May 3rd-Goldfinches. May 9th-Rose Breasted Grosbeaks and Scarlet Tanangers. May 11th-Hummingbirds. May 19th-Orioles.
Sunny-light wind and 80 degrees. Saw osprey circling looking for food. Lots of weeds in the North end of lake.
Sunny - moderate wind- 75 degrees. North end of lake choked with weeds. Many on the surface.
Sunny - moderate wind- temperature was 76 degrees
Sunny - light wind - 75 degrees - Saw 1 loon near the boat landing and 1 loon North of the island.
65 degrees with moderate wind. Ice on lake from 11/30/2011 to 03/22/2012.

column1: First sightings: Goldfinch - March 1st- Geese - March 12th- Redwing Blackbirds
and Robins - March 14th- Porcupine - March 21st- Loon - March 22nd- Flicker - April 1sdt.

column2: 74 degrees sunny and light wind- yellow bloom on water neer shore. First sightings: spring peepers and tree frogs - April 2. Rose Breasted Grosbeak - May 7- Orioles - May 10. Hummingbird - May 10. Lilacs Bloom - May 13. Bull Frogs - June 1.

Mostly sunny + hot- saw 5 loons. 2 adults in North end and 1 adult and 2 unknown loons in the South end. Too far away to see if they were adults or chicks. Lots of weeds in the North end with some on top of the water.
Beautiful sunny day- 75 degrees. Saw 2 herons.
Beautiful fall day. 50 degrees with a light wind.
Sunny and 43 degrees. Water level very high and water very dark.

Hazy sun 65 degrees- Gilmore ice out 5/7/2013- had 8 wild turkeys at feeder all winter until May 1st. Lots of dead panfish on shoreline. First sightings: 4/4 Redwing Blackbirds- 4/6 Racoon- 4/16 Geese and Ducks- 4/17 Juncos-

column1: 4/24 Robin- 5/5 Loon- 5/5 Peeper Frogs- 5/14 Black Bear- 5/19 Hummingbirds and Orioles- 5/22 Rose Breasted Grosbeaks.

column2: clear-light wind-76 degrees-dragonfly hatch June 3rd-heard first bullfrogs June 12th
Hazy sun 74 degrees Saw an adult loon with 1 chick.
76 degrees- very humid-didn't see any wildlife. Still have hummingbirds at feeder.
Sunny and clear- 58 degrees. Saw 4 loons at the North end of the lake.
Clear-Sunny 45 degrees. Saw no wildlife but tamaracks very colorful.
Sunny- 69 degrees- saw 1 muskrat- ice out April 12- first spring peepers heard April 15- hummingbirds and orioles returned May 17- dragonfly hatch May 19.
Clear and sunny 75 degrees. Saw 2 loons in south end of lake. Lots of weeds in the north end of lake.
